Imagine you’re in the studio and THAT’S what a Songwriter of the Year GRAMMY Nominee says to you 🤯 

Theron Thomas (@therontheron_) has written hits with some of your favorite artists including Beyoncé, Doja Cat, Justin Bieber, Nicki Minaj, Usher, Latto, Lizzo, Lil Durk / J. Cole, Rihanna and more! 

In this episode, he shares his formula for hit records, a theory about why people think “today’s music sucks”, his thoughts on a controversial Quincy Jones quote, where most songwriters are falling short, and much more 🔂

Full interview w/ @therontheron_ OUT NOW 🔗 

#musicpodcast #songwriter #singersongwriter #musicbusiness #musicbiz #grammyawards #grammys

When you’re a GRAMMY nominee for Songwriter of the Year, it’s easy to say “F*ck everybody. I’M HIM.”

The fact Theron Thomas wakes up and eats a slice of humble 🥧 instead is probably why he’s risen to the top 📈 

This interview is a must-watch‼️ FULL EPISODE OUT NOW 🔗

Thanks to social media, FANS are the new A&Rs. Is that GOOD or BAD for the music industry? 🧐

On one hand, there’s much less gatekeeping. ANYONE with an internet connection can record, distribute, and market music globally. 🌎 

On the OTHER hand, many argue that it’s why the quality of music is suffering. 📉
